# AI Agent Custom Rules

1. **ALWAYS** start by reading the `README.md` file at the root of the project before answering questions, analyzing code, or making any code changes in any conversation.
2. Pay special attention to the "Database Modification Rules" section in the README.
3. NEVER modify the base `.sql` files located in the `Database/` folder (`war_accounts.sql`, `war_characters.sql`, `war_world.sql`).
4. ALWAYS create a new update script (e.g., `update_001.sql`) for any database modifications and clearly instruct the user to apply it before launching the emulator.
5. Compile checks must happen before moving to the next task. This requirement can be bypassed if multiple steps need to happen before compile and QA check.
6. If you (the AI Agent) are instructed to modify this file (`.cursorrules`), you MUST immediately run the `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\Sync-Airules.ps1` command afterward to ensure all other agent custom rules files are synchronized.

